    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### 📊 Lead Qualification Rules\n\n**Scoring Breakdown (Max 100 points):**\n* **Domain Quality (30 pts):** Corporate Email = 30 pts | Consumer Email (Gmail/Yahoo) = 5 pts\n* **Project Budget (40 pts):** ≥ $5k = 40 pts | ≥ $2k = 25 pts | > $0 = 10 pts\n* **Company Scale (20 pts):** ≥ 100 emp = 20 pts | ≥ 10 emp = 10 pts | > 0 emp = 5 pts\n* **Description Richness (10 pts):** > 150 chars = 10 pts | > 50 chars = 5 pts\n\n**🔀 Routing Threshold:**\n* **Branch 0 (High Value):** Score ≥ 50 ➔ Triggers AI personalization & instant alert.\n* **Branch 1 (Low Priority):** Score < 50 ➔ Logs to spreadsheet quietly.",
        "height": 384,
        "width": 544
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        288,
        496
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "ff1b9785-21a6-4631-b6ce-e3a0610db961",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Loop through all incoming items from Enrich Lead Data\nfor (const item of $input.all()) {\n  \n  // 1. Safely access the organization data object\n  const organization = item.json.organization || {};\n  \n  // 2. Extract the domain directly from Apollo's payload\n  const domain = organization.primary_domain || \"\";\n  \n  // 3. List of common public consumer email domains to filter out\n  const consumerDomains = [\n    'gmail.com', 'yahoo.com', 'hotmail.com', 'outlook.com', \n    'icloud.com', 'protonmail.com', 'aol.com', 'zoho.com'\n  ];\n\n  // 4. Evaluate if it's a corporate domain\n  let isCorporate = false;\n  if (domain && !consumerDomains.includes(domain.toLowerCase())) {\n    isCorporate = true;\n  }\n\n  // 5. Calculate the headcount by summing the departments (equals 163)\n  const departments = organization.departmental_head_count || {};\n  let totalCompanySize = Object.values(departments).reduce((sum, count) => sum + count, 0);\n  \n  // Fallback: If departmental breakdown is missing, use Apollo's high-level estimate (180)\n  if (totalCompanySize === 0) {\n    totalCompanySize = organization.estimated_num_employees || 0;\n  }\n\n  // 6. Append the new values directly into the existing item payload\n  // This ensures you don't lose name, budget, or project descriptions!\n  item.json.is_corporate_domain = isCorporate;\n  item.json.company_size = totalCompanySize;\n  \n  // Backfill the domain root field if it isn't there already\n  if (!item.json.domain && domain) {\n    item.json.domain = domain;\n  }\n}\n\n// Pass the enriched items down the pipeline\nreturn $input.all();"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        288,
        976
      ],
      "id": "d6ff706f-afdb-4fd1-a4ec-477abf836a5f",
      "name": "Evaluate Domain Quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Loop through all incoming items from Assess Domain Quality\nfor (const item of $input.all()) {\n  \n  // 1. Use .first().json to bypass n8n's item-pairing tracking bug\n  let leadData = {};\n  try {\n    leadData = $('Normalize Lead Data').first().json;\n  } catch (e) {\n    leadData = item.json; // Backup fallback\n  }\n  \n  // 2. FIXED: Pull company name directly from the Typeform Trigger node\n  let companyName = \"\";\n  try {\n    const typeformData = $('Typeform Trigger').first().json;\n    // Checks multiple common casing styles depending on how you typed it in Typeform\n    companyName = typeformData[\"Company Name\"] || \n                  typeformData[\"Company name\"] || \n                  typeformData[\"company\"] || \n                  typeformData[\"company_name\"] || \n                  leadData.company || \"\"; \n  } catch (e) {\n    companyName = leadData.company || \"\"; // Ultimate backup fallback\n  }\n\n  // 3. Map core identity fields using your exact updated casing properties\n  const name = leadData.Name || leadData.name || leadData[\"What is your full name?\"] || \"\";\n  const email = leadData.Email || leadData.email || leadData[\"What is your business or primary email address?\"] || \"\";\n  const domain = item.json.domain || leadData.domain || leadData[\"What is your company's website or domain?\"] || \"\";\n  \n  // 4. Extract budget and description details\n  const budget = Number(leadData.Budget || leadData.budget || leadData[\"What is your estimated development budget range?\"]) || 0;\n  const projectDesc = leadData[\"Project Description\"] || leadData.project_description || leadData[\"Please describe your project or operational bottleneck.\"] || \"\";\n  \n  // 5. Pull quality metrics calculated in the previous node step\n  const isCorporate = item.json.is_corporate_domain === true;\n  const totalCompanySize = Number(item.json.company_size) || 0;\n\n  // 6. Calculate Lead Score\n  let score = 0;\n\n  // Rule A: Email Domain Quality (Max 30 pts)\n  if (isCorporate) {\n    score += 30;\n  } else {\n    score += 5; \n  }\n\n  // Rule B: Estimated Project Budget (Max 40 pts)\n  if (budget >= 5000) {\n    score += 40;\n  } else if (budget >= 2000) {\n    score += 25;\n  } else if (budget > 0) {\n    score += 10;\n  }\n\n  // Rule C: Company Scale / Employee Headcount (Max 20 pts)\n  if (totalCompanySize >= 100) {\n    score += 20; \n  } else if (totalCompanySize >= 10) {\n    score += 10; \n  } else if (totalCompanySize > 0) {\n    score += 5;   \n  }\n\n  // Rule D: Request Richness / Description Length (Max 10 pts)\n  if (projectDesc.trim().length > 150) {\n    score += 10; \n  } else if (projectDesc.trim().length > 50) {\n    score += 5;\n  }\n\n  // Restrict score boundaries between 0 and 100\n  score = Math.max(0, Math.min(score, 100));\n\n  // 7. Reconstruct the object with 100% of the required data fields populated\n  item.json = {\n    name: name,\n    email: email,\n    company: companyName,\n    domain: isCorporate && domain ? domain : \"NA\", // <-- FIXED: Outputs \"NA\" if is_corporate_domain is false or empty\n    project_description: projectDesc,\n    budget: budget,\n    is_corporate_domain: isCorporate,\n    company_size: totalCompanySize,\n    lead_score: score\n  };\n}\n\n// Return the completely unified data object down the pipeline\nreturn $input.all();"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        512,
        976
      ],
      "id": "61670bef-989a-420d-b742-b542033fbf9f",
      "name": "Calculate Lead Score"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a senior B2B Sales Consultant and AI Automation Strategist.\n\nYour objective is to help a salesperson quickly understand a qualified lead and create a personalized outreach strategy that maximizes the chances of booking a discovery call.\n\n## Lead Information\n\nName: {{ $json.name }}\n\nEmail: {{ $json.email }}\n\nCompany: {{ $json.company }}\n\nEmail Domain: {{ $json.domain }}\n\nCompany Size: {{ $json.company_size }}\n\nLead Score: {{ $json.lead_score }}\n\nBudget: ${{ $json.budget }}\n\nProject Description:\n{{ $json.project_description }}\n\n---\n\nAnalyze the lead using only the information provided.\n\nGenerate a practical outreach strategy that a salesperson can use immediately.\n\nGuidelines:\n\n* Determine whether the lead priority is High, Medium, or Low.\n* Summarize the lead in one concise sentence.\n* Identify up to three likely business pain points.\n* Recommend an automation or AI solution that directly addresses those pain points.\n* Explain the business value of the proposed solution.\n* Choose the best outreach channel (Email, LinkedIn, Phone, or Email then LinkedIn).\n* Write a concise outreach strategy focused on solving the lead's business problem.\n* Create a personalized opening sentence for the first outreach email.\n* Generate a short and compelling email subject line.\n* Suggest a clear call to action that encourages a discovery call.\n* Recommend the best follow-up action if there is no reply within a few business days.\n* Estimate an appropriate project value based on the lead's budget, company size, and project complexity.\n* Assign a confidence score between 1 and 100.\n\nDo not invent facts about the company. Base all recommendations on reasonable inferences from the supplied information.\n\nFollow the output schema provided by the Structured Output Parser.\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
